
[1]abstain

   ABSTA'IN, v.i. [L. abstineo, to keep from; abs and teneo, to hold. See
   Tenant.]

   In a general sense, to forbear, or refrain from, voluntarily; but used
   chiefly to denote a restraint upon the passions or appetites; to
   refrain from indulgence.

   Abstain from meats offered to idols. Acts, xv.

   To abstain from the use of ardent spirits; to abstain from luxuries.
